history.text: Hello
Hello. I enjoyed watching Catch Me If You Can with Leonardo DiCaprio, did you?
Yes, I did. I'm amazed at what he did all at age 19.
He must have looked older than 19 to fake being a doctor.
What did you like about it?
I agree. I can't believe how much money he ended up conning out of people.
And Leonardo DiCaprio and Tom Hanks are always enjoyable in any movie.
I like it that the film was about a real person.
Yes, Tom Hanks is one of my favorite actors.
I like movies that portray that type of behavior in a fun way without taking it too seriously.
I like Amy Adams too.
Yes, I agree, I like a film that can have both serious content, and some levity.
She is always entertaining.
It is so impressive that Frank was able to impersonate such highly technical professions as medicine and law. He must be a consummate liar.
I can't believe it's possible to impersonate an airline pilot.
Oh, yes! That is inconceivable!
I guess all it takes is confidence and desperation.
I don't have the tool kit to do any of that. Do you?
I can't imagine most of the things he manages to do. I am a teacher, so I might be able to do that one, but I don't knwo French.
Overall, I really enjoyed this film and I will watch it again.
I am glad that he got caught, though. And it's good that he managed to be turned into an asset for the FBI.
Yes, that is the best part of it, that he was able to redeem himself and go on to do good work for society.
I wish I knew what happened to the real Frank--whether he stayed with the FBI or went back to crime.
We can Google him when we're done.
Good idea.
Oh, I guess he did stay with the FBI. He got married and had children.
I wonder where you can buy his unforgable checks.
Yeah, I had already looked him up, but wasn't sure it was okay to discuss it here.
The newest paragraph has that information.
Oh, whoopsie.
I'm glad we found out without breaking the rules.
It was sad, the broken relationship he had with his dad. It must be tough to have a parent like that.
It is. I'm glad that he managed to have a stable family himself.
It was great that Carl became a sort of father figure for him. It shows Frank's intelligence and willingness to change, that he could adapt to a better life.

It kind of gives you hope the your own loved ones who are struggling still have a chance to turn their lives around. I mean, if someone as deep into trouble as Frank is can do it, then maybe others can too.

uid1response.feedback: This is my first chat, and I hope to do more. Feedback is appreciated if possible.
